Your chance to visit a real working dairy farm! Be sure to mark your calendars for the 2013 Kenosha County Dairy Breakfast on June 15, 2013. You just might run into some friendly, familiar faces from your local Community State Bank office. We'll be cooking eggs in a 6ft. skillet from 8:00am - 10:30am. This annual event is fun for the whole family! Enjoy a morning on the farm that includes: a big farm breakfast, milking demonstrations, a Wisconsin products tent, old-fashioned children's games and much more! The breakfast will include scrambled eggs with ham and cheese, pancakes, fresh bread and butter, yogurt, muffin, milk, juice, and ice cream. Admission to the farm is free. Breakfast tickets are $6 and children 6 and under eat free. Kenosha County Dairy Breakfast Uhlenhake’s Land-Locked Acres 1801 216th Ave. Union Grove, WI 53182
